{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bfda2520-1884-4e71-ab7b-fcd86ba003c0","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr equivalently:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"ClassName=ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nThe first form matches any test whose fully qualified name contains \"ReportExporterTests\". The second form filters by exact class name. Both will exclude `ReportGeneratorTests`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3b03cb20-10aa-4762-b6fb-87dd298f6660","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only the `ReportExporterTests` class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question about the `dotnet test` CLI command filtering.\n\nThe answer is to use the `--filter` option with a fully qualified class name or just the class name.","outputTokens":181,"requestId":"BC33:2D1C62:298629:306F03:69FA94F6"},"id":"64a6c64f-68b7-496d-a8a9-9f67bb16c322","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:10:19.137Z","parentId":"f463d66b-299a-45cd-bf28-3f065d4e543f"}
